When you give yourself to your craft I’ve learned so much about life through it. End goal is to always have my guest happy then secondly I want to make sure I’m content with what gets put out. 
Much like life and this clip if your are too determined on your vision, too laser focused, it stops other possibilities from happening, because of our ego and pride we think it should always happen on our first attempt. Here I took down and restarted my braid 3-4 times. Much like life we don’t win on our first attempt and that’s ok understanding when to pause and restart is just as important if not more. Being open to different approaches can lead to better results. You just do what works. Even better way to look at the times it didn’t work, it was a learning experience. And at the end it only an extra 5-10mins. Most client do appreciate  giving our best vs being the fastest . Although that’s pretty cool too . ☺️

Hello everyone! The time has come for me to carry onto my next journey, I’m moving back to my home city in Las Vegas, NV. Words can’t express what this city has done for me the last 7 years. Mostly good, because life isn’t perfect but all opportunities to learn and grow in all aspects. I have found/discovered soooo much and never want to lose it. Which was a goal of mine when I moved to LA. Thank you to all lovely ladies I have had the pleasure of working with, working my craft on, working besides, and those whose who have aloud for me to share my story. 
Thank you for each friend, colleague, my salon @unionsalon, for this experience. 
•••SALON CLIENTS I will return every last Thursday to Sunday of each month continue to book with me when I’m available. I will post travel dates in bio and as they come. And would love to continue see you all but understand not everyone will be able to fit my travel schedule. Please reach out to me to help pair you with a new stylist if needed and any questions.
Personal update: My partner, @sonnyshazam, will remain here in Pasadena. While I start this next chapter for us. 🤍
Last day here is March 25th I’m not sure what more to include. Just leaving so grateful and blessed for this opportunity.

Using some of my favorite @oribe products must haves. 
 • Oribe Mystify •
Restyling spray: love using in dry 2nd day hair to reshape the hair. Getting rid of any stubborn bends. Prior to blow drying on dry hair.

• Oribe Balm d’Or •
Heat Styling Shield
Primarily use to smooth out blonde ends or frizzy hair but in her case I concentrated on hairline to help control those baby hairs. Can be used on wet or dry hair 

 • Oribe Thick •
Dry Finishing Spray: used to add touchable texture and help hair appear thicker. Can be used before or after hot tools

Throw in a braided bun and viola 🙌
All products provide 450 degree protection

Today I turn 30. These past few years I have found myself going into another world but only to discover I’m coming back to this reality.
i find so much not with my eyes, but by listening, observing, feeling, discovering, reflecting and letting go… not in any specific order. life can distract us from doing so. How often do I practice this through? With others and with myself. Definitely more these days. 
What’s this have to do with this random yoga post? 
Well this is where I found it. Paying attention how I speak to myself, to my body. I find my silence, I find peace and sooo much more.

Some of the girlies get it, some don’t. More men should. But I’m grateful for all those who support and encourage me in this journey of life. 🤍

I’ve have tagged some of my great teachers⬆️

Man being a hairstylist is pretty hard on the body especially those HOURS long projects WHILE STANDING! Shorties with upper body aches and pains and the taller guys(+girls) with lower. Amongst our hands and shoulder forearms, hamstrings etc.  getting chronically tight from repetitive motions. 
so taking care of my body is a requirement (I now understand). Leaning more creative through life I never really understood how i moved within my body but there’s so much learn learn. So I’m trying to get creative with it. If you give back to it, it will give so much in return. Anyways thought I share some Geraldo things i do outside the salon. #LasVegasHairSalon #LasVegasHairstylist
